Durban - Seven people, including three Home Affairs officials were arrested by Hawks members from the Durban Crime Unit and Home Affairs Counter Corruption Team for fraud, contravention of Immigration Act and Identification Act. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said the Home Affairs Counter Corruption Team had discovered that there were some irregularities in the issuing of late birth certificates at uMzimkhulu, Bulwer and Ulundi Home Affairs offices. From 18 August 2017 to 1 September 2017, members embarked on an operation where the seven were arrested. “Snothile Buthelezi (26), Sibulelo Malanda (49), Buyelaphi Stubchen (57), Nkosinathi Madlala (31), Nokuphiwa Fihlane (26), Nowinile Sikhosana (34) and Lindiswa Mkhafula (28) briefly appeared in the Durban Special Commercial Crime Court on Thursday, 31 August 2017. They were granted R2000.00 bail each and the case was postponed to 3 November 2017,” said Mhlongo. Stubchen appeared on Monday, 4 September and her case was postponed to October 5. Daily News